## Phases `[FIXED]` structure, `[DYNAMIC]` content

Before each phase, read the relevant .md file rather than invent how to work. If you don't like the content, or think it needs to evolve, you can change it. But read it first to understand the precedent.

| Phase   | File                | Purpose                                            |
| ------- | ------------------- | -------------------------------------------------- |
| Plan    | `phases/plan.md`    | Context + massive parallel discovery + workplan    |
| Execute | `phases/execute.md` | Massive parallel execution in worktrees            |
| Reflect | `phases/reflect.md` | Test + prevent + consolidate + ship                |

**Coherency mode** (every Nth tick): Same 3 phases, but Plan does strategic discovery (research, audit, rotation, **semantic review via REVIEW.md agents**) and Reflect adds deep self-improvement (rejuvenation agents, constitution review, REVIEW.md evolution).

## Two Testing Layers `[FIXED]`

1. **Deterministic tests** — run every Reflect. vitest/pytest/cargo test. Binary pass/fail. Catch exact regressions.
2. **Semantic review** (`REVIEW.md`) — run every coherency round. 3-8 agents review all changes since last coherency against semantic rules (interpretability, feedback surfaces, UX quality, tone). Catch quality/intent issues tests can't express.

Both layers are mandatory. Deterministic tests gate every ship. Semantic review gates coherency promotion.

